25/******** IR Module ********/
26
27const PrimFuncNode* GetRootPrimFunc(const IRModule& mod, const StmtNode* root_block,
28 GlobalVar* result_g_var) {
29 for (const auto& kv : mod->functions) {
30 const GlobalVar& g_var = kv.first;
31 const BaseFunc& base_func = kv.second;
32 if (const auto* func = base_func.as<PrimFuncNode>()) {
33 if (const auto* realize = func->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
34 if (realize->block.get() == root_block) {
35 if (result_g_var != nullptr) {
36 *result_g_var = g_var;
37 }
38 return func;
39 }
40 }
41 }
42 }
43 LOG(FATAL) << "IndexError: Could not get the corresponding function in the schedule state of the "
44 "statement:\n"
45 << GetRef<Stmt>(root_block);
46 throw;
47}

49/******** Scope ********/
50
51StmtSRef GetScopeRoot(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& sref,
52 bool require_stage_pipeline) {
53 class RootBlockError : public ScheduleError {
54 public:
55 explicit RootBlockError(IRModule mod) : mod_(mod) {}
56 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
57 String FastErrorString() const final {
58 return "ScheduleError: The primitive does not operate on the root block";
59 }
60 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
61 return "The primitive does not operate on the root block";
62 }
63 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {}; }
64 IRModule mod_;
65 };
66
67 class NotStagePipelineError : public ScheduleError {
68 public:
69 explicit NotStagePipelineError(IRModule mod, Block block) : mod_(mod), block_(block) {}
70 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
71 String FastErrorString() const final {
72 return "ScheduleError: The scope root is not a stage pipeline";
73 }
74 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
75 return R"(The scope {0} is not a stage pipeline.
76Definition of a scope that is a stage pipeline:
77- The region cover property holds for every of its child blocks
78- No write-after-read dependency or opaque dependency,
79- only read-after-write and write-after-write are allowed
80- All the statements in the scope are schedulable statements, i.e. Block and For
81)";
82 }
83 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
84 IRModule mod_;
85 Block block_;
86 };
87
88 StmtSRef scope_root_sref{nullptr};
89 StmtSRef scope_root_subtree{nullptr};
90 // Step 1. Find the scope root and the subtree that the given sref is in
91 {
92 const StmtSRefNode* p = sref->parent;
93 const StmtSRefNode* subtree = sref.get();
94 for (; p != nullptr; subtree = p, p = p->parent) {
95 if (p->stmt->IsInstance<BlockNode>()) {
96 scope_root_sref = GetRef<StmtSRef>(p);
97 scope_root_subtree = GetRef<StmtSRef>(subtree);
98 break;
99 }
100 }
101 if (p == nullptr) {
102 throw RootBlockError(self->mod);
103 }
104 }
105 // Step 2. Handle `require_stage_pipeline`
106 if (require_stage_pipeline) {
107 bool stage_pipeline = self->GetBlockInfo(scope_root_sref).scope->stage_pipeline;
108 if (stage_pipeline == false) {
109 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_root_sref);
110 throw NotStagePipelineError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block));
111 }
112 }
113 return scope_root_sref;
114}
115
116ScopeBlockLoopInfo GetScopeBlockLoopInfo(const Block& scope_block) {
117 struct Collector : public StmtVisitor {
118 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* realize) final {
119 result.realizes.push_back(GetRef<BlockRealize>(realize));
120 const Array<IterVar>& iter_vars = realize->block->iter_vars;
121 const Array<PrimExpr>& iter_values = realize->iter_values;
122 ICHECK_EQ(iter_vars.size(), iter_values.size());
123 int n = realize->iter_values.size();
124 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
125 const IterVar& iter_var = iter_vars[i];
126 const PrimExpr& iter_value = iter_values[i];
127 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* vars = nullptr;
128 if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
129 vars = &result.spatial_vars;
130 } else {
131 vars = &result.non_spatial_vars;
132 }
133 PostOrderVisit(iter_value, [vars](const ObjectRef& obj) {
134 if (const VarNode* var = obj.as<VarNode>()) {
135 vars->insert(var);
136 }
137 });
138 }
139 }
140
141 ScopeBlockLoopInfo result;
142 } visitor;
143 visitor(scope_block->body);
144 return std::move(visitor.result);
145}

147/*!
148 * \brief Check whether the given sref_a is higher than or equal to sref_b.
149 */
150void CheckSRefHigherOrEqual(const StmtSRef& sref_a, const StmtSRef& sref_b) {
151 const StmtSRefNode* p = sref_b.get();
152 for (; p != nullptr; p = p->parent) {
153 if (p == sref_a.get()) {
154 return;
155 }
156 }
157 CHECK(false) << "Expect StmtSRef " << sref_a << "to be higher than or equal to " << sref_b;
158}

160/*!
161 * \brief Check the dominant property of a block:
162 * the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers under the
163 * given root scope.
164 * \param self The schedule state.
165 * \param scope_root_sref The StmtSRef corresponding to the root scope.
166 * \param block_sref The block whose dominant property is to be checked.
167 * \return A boolean indicating if the block is a dominant block.
168 */
169bool IsDominantBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref,
170 const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
171 std::unordered_map<Buffer, Array<StmtSRef>, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> buffer_writers;
172 CheckSRefHigherOrEqual(scope_root_sref, block_sref);
173 const BlockNode* maybe_root_block = scope_root_sref->StmtAs<BlockNode>();
174 if (maybe_root_block) {
175 BlockScope scope = self->GetBlockScope(scope_root_sref);
176 buffer_writers = scope->buffer_writers;
177 } else {
178 // Collect all child blocks of root sub-tree, and merge their buffer writers.
179 Array<StmtSRef> child_block_srefs = GetChildBlockSRefOnSRefTree(self, scope_root_sref);
180 for (const StmtSRef& child_block_sref : child_block_srefs) {
181 BlockScope child_scope = self->GetBlockScope(child_block_sref);
182 for (const auto& it : child_scope->buffer_writers) {
183 buffer_writers.insert(it);
184 }
185 }
186 }
187 // Check whether the input block is the only writer of its outputs
188 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
189 for (const BufferRegion& write_region : block->writes) {
190 if (buffer_writers.count(write_region->buffer)) {
191 if (buffer_writers.at(write_region->buffer).size() != 1) {
192 return false;
193 }
194 }
195 }
196 return true;
197}

199/*!
200 * \brief A helper function that checks whether a given block is a complete block under the scope,
201 * or return the condition it violates if it is not a complete block
202 * \param self The schedule state
203 * \param block_sref The block to be checked
204 * \param scope_root_sref The sref to the root block of the scope that `block_sref` is in
205 * \return 0 if the block is a complete block, or a positive integer indicating which condition is
206 * first violated
207 */
208int CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
209 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
210 // Cond 1. All block vars are data parallel
211 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
212 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
213 if (iter_var->iter_type != kDataPar) {
214 return 1;
215 }
216 }
217 // Cond 2. Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output,
218 // dominating the reader of its output buffers
219 if (!IsDominantBlock(self, scope_root_sref, block_sref)) {
220 return 2;
221 }
222 // Cond 3. No overlap between the buffers the block reads and writes
223 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> written_buffers;
224 written_buffers.reserve(block->writes.size());
225 for (const BufferRegion& write : block->writes) {
226 written_buffers.insert(write->buffer.get());
227 }
228 for (const BufferRegion& read : block->reads) {
229 if (written_buffers.count(read->buffer.get())) {
230 return 3;
231 }
232 }
233 return 0;
234}
235
236static const char* kCompleteBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a complete block:
2371) All block vars are data parallel
2382) Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers
2393) No overlap between the buffers the block reads and writes)";
240
241static const char* kReductionBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a reduction block:
2421) The block has the `init` statement
2432) All the block bindings are quasi-affine expressions
2443) All block vars are either data parallel block vars or reduction block vars
2454) Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers
2465) The reduction block vars are not used to index the output buffers)";
247
248static const char* kLocalCompleteBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a local complete block:
2491) All block vars are data parallel
2502) Local Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers under a given subtree
2513) No overlap between the buffers the block reads and writes)";
252
253static const char* kLocalReductionBlockDefinition = R"(Definition of a reduction block:
2541) The block has the `init` statement
2552) All the block bindings are quasi-affine expressions
2563) All block vars are either data parallel block vars or reduction block vars
2574) Local Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its output buffers under a given subtree
2585) The reduction block vars are not used to index the output buffers)";
259
260bool IsCompleteBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
261 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
262 return CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref) == 0;
263}
264
265void CheckCompleteBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
266 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
267 class IncompleteBlockError : public ScheduleError {
268 public:
269 explicit IncompleteBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block, int violated_cond)
270 : mod_(std::move(mod)), block_(std::move(block)), violated_cond_(violated_cond) {}
271 String FastErrorString() const final { return "ScheduleError: Incomplete block"; }
272 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
273 std::ostringstream os;
274 os << "The block {0} is not a complete block - it violates condition #" << violated_cond_;
275 os << ".\n" << kCompleteBlockDefinition;
276 return os.str();
277 }
278 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
279 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
280 IRModule mod_;
281 Block block_;
282 int violated_cond_;
283 };
284
285 int error_code = CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
286 if (error_code != 0) {
287 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
288 throw IncompleteBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block), error_code);
289 }
290}

292/*!
293 * \brief A helper function that checks whether a given block is a reduction block under the scope,
294 * or return the condition it violates if it is not a reduction block
295 * \param self The schedule state
296 * \param block_sref The block to be checked
297 * \param scope_root_sref The sref to the root block of the scope that `block_sref` is in
298 * \return 0 if the block is a reduction block, or a positive integer indicating which condition is
299 * first violated
300 */
301int CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
302 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
303 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
304 // Cond 1. The block has the `init` statement.
305 if (!block->init.defined()) {
306 return 1;
307 }
308 // Cond 2. All the block bindings are quasi-affine expressions.
309 if (!self->IsAffineBlockBinding(block_sref)) {
310 return 2;
311 }
312 // Cond 3. All block vars are either data parallel block vars or reduction block vars. Meanwhile,
313 // we collect all the reduction block vars.
314 if (!ContainsOnlyDataParAndReductionBlockIter(block->iter_vars)) {
315 return 3;
316 }
317 // Cond 4. Dominant: the block is the only writer of its output, dominating the reader of its
318 // output buffers.
319 if (!IsDominantBlock(self, scope_root_sref, block_sref)) {
320 return 4;
321 }
322 // Cond 5. The reduction block vars are not used to index the output buffers.
323 return ReductionIterNotIndexOutputBuffer(GetRef<Block>(block)) ? 0 : 5;
324}
325
326bool IsReductionBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
327 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
328 return CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref) == 0;
329}

331void CheckReductionBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
332 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
333 class NotReductionBlockError : public ScheduleError {
334 public:
335 explicit NotReductionBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block, int violated_cond)
336 : mod_(std::move(mod)), block_(std::move(block)), violated_cond_(violated_cond) {}
337 String FastErrorString() const final { return "ScheduleError: Not a reduction block"; }
338 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
339 std::ostringstream os;
340 os << "The block {0} is not a reduction block - it violates condition #" << violated_cond_;
341 os << ".\n" << kReductionBlockDefinition;
342 return os.str();
343 }
344 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
345 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
346 IRModule mod_;
347 Block block_;
348 int violated_cond_;
349 };
350
351 int error_code = CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
352 if (error_code != 0) {
353 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
354 throw NotReductionBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block), error_code);
355 }
356}

358void CheckCompleteOrReductionBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
359 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
360 class NotCompleteOrReductionBlockError : public ScheduleError {
361 public:
362 explicit NotCompleteOrReductionBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block,
363 int complete_block_error_code,
364 int reduction_block_error_code)
365 : mod_(mod),
366 block_(block),
367 complete_block_error_code_(complete_block_error_code),
368 reduction_block_error_code_(reduction_block_error_code) {}
369
370 String FastErrorString() const final {
371 return "ScheduleError: Not a complete or reduction block";
372 }
373 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
374 std::ostringstream os;
375 os << "The block {0} is not a complete block - it violates condition #"
376 << complete_block_error_code_;
377 os << ".\n" << kCompleteBlockDefinition;
378 os << "\nThe block is not a reduction block either - it violates condition #"
379 << reduction_block_error_code_;
380 os << ".\n" << kReductionBlockDefinition;
381 return os.str();
382 }
383 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
384 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
385
386 IRModule mod_;
387 Block block_;
388 int complete_block_error_code_;
389 int reduction_block_error_code_;
390 };
391
392 int complete_block_error_code = CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
393 if (complete_block_error_code == 0) {
394 return;
395 }
396 int reduction_block_error_code = CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref);
397 if (reduction_block_error_code == 0) {
398 return;
399 }
400 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
401 throw NotCompleteOrReductionBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block), complete_block_error_code,
402 reduction_block_error_code);
403}

405void CheckSubtreeCompactDataflow(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& subtree_root) {
406 class NotCompactDataFlowError : public ScheduleError {
407 public:
408 explicit NotCompactDataFlowError(IRModule mod, Stmt subtree_root, Block violate_block,
409 int local_complete_block_code, int local_reduction_block_code)
410 : mod_(std::move(mod)),
411 subtree_root_(std::move(subtree_root)),
412 violate_block_(std::move(violate_block)),
413 local_complete_block_code_(local_complete_block_code),
414 local_reduction_block_code_(local_reduction_block_code) {
415 ICHECK(subtree_root_->IsInstance<BlockNode>() || subtree_root_->IsInstance<ForNode>());
416 }
417 String FastErrorString() const final {
418 return "ScheduleError: The queried subtree root in SRef tree does not have compact dataflow, "
419 "because some of its child block on SRef tree is neither a local complete block nor a "
420 "local reduction block.";
421 }
422 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
423 std::ostringstream os;
424 os << "The queried subtree root {0} in SRef tree does not have compact dataflow, because "
425 "its child block {1} on SRef tree is neither a local complete block nor a local "
426 "reduction block.\n";
427 os << "It violates condition #" << local_complete_block_code_
428 << " as a local complete block.\n";
429 os << kLocalCompleteBlockDefinition << "\n";
430 os << "It violates condition #" << local_reduction_block_code_
431 << " as a local reduction block.\n";
432 os << kLocalReductionBlockDefinition << "\n";
433 return os.str();
434 }
435 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
436 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {subtree_root_, violate_block_}; }
437
438 IRModule mod_;
439 Stmt subtree_root_;
440 Block violate_block_;
441 int local_complete_block_code_;
442 int local_reduction_block_code_;
443 };
444
445 Array<StmtSRef> child_block_srefs = GetChildBlockSRefOnSRefTree(self, subtree_root);
446 for (const StmtSRef& block_sref : child_block_srefs) {
447 int local_complete_block_code = CheckCompleteBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, subtree_root),
448 local_reduction_block_code = CheckReductionBlockErrorCode(self, block_sref, subtree_root);
449 if (local_complete_block_code != 0 && local_reduction_block_code != 0) {
450 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
451 throw NotCompactDataFlowError(self->mod, GetRef<Stmt>(subtree_root->stmt),
452 GetRef<Block>(block), local_complete_block_code,
453 local_reduction_block_code);
454 }
455 }
456}

458bool IsOutputBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
459 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
460 const BlockNode* scope_root = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_root_sref);
461 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
462 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> scope_allocated;
463 scope_allocated.reserve(scope_root->alloc_buffers.size());
464 for (const Buffer& buffer : scope_root->alloc_buffers) {
465 scope_allocated.insert(buffer.get());
466 }
467 for (const BufferRegion& buffer_region : block->writes) {
468 if (!scope_allocated.count(buffer_region->buffer.get())) {
469 return true;
470 }
471 }
472 return false;
473}

475void CheckNotOutputBlock(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
476 const StmtSRef& scope_root_sref) {
477 class OutputBlockError : public ScheduleError {
478 public:
479 explicit OutputBlockError(IRModule mod, Block block) : mod_(mod), block_(block) {}
480 String FastErrorString() const final {
481 return "ScheduleError: Cannot operate on an output block";
482 }
483 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final { return "The block {0} is an output block"; }
484 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
485 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
486
487 IRModule mod_;
488 Block block_;
489 };
490 if (IsOutputBlock(self, block_sref, scope_root_sref)) {
491 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
492 throw OutputBlockError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block));
493 }
494}

496std::vector<IterVarType> GetBlockVarTypes(const BlockNode* block) {
497 std::vector<IterVarType> results;
498 results.reserve(block->iter_vars.size());
499 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
500 results.push_back(iter_var->iter_type);
501 }
502 return results;
503}
504
505std::vector<IterVarType> GetBlockVarTypes(const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
506 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
507 return GetBlockVarTypes(block);
508}
509
510bool IsWriteCache(const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
511 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
512 if (block->writes.size() != 1) {
513 return false;
514 }
515 const BufferRegion& write_region = block->writes[0];
516 for (const BufferRegion& read_region : block->reads) {
517 auto [exists, surjective, injective, ordered, no_const_read, no_shift_read] =
518 AnalyzeReadWritePattern(read_region, write_region);
519 // https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=81767
520 (void)exists;
521 (void)surjective;
522 (void)no_const_read;
523 (void)no_shift_read;
524 if (!(injective && ordered)) {
525 return false;
526 }
527 }
528 return true;
529}

531/******** Binding ********/
532
533bool IsAffineBinding(const BlockRealize& realize, const Map<Var, Range>& loop_var_ranges,
534 arith::Analyzer* analyzer) {
535 if (loop_var_ranges.empty()) {
536 return true;
537 }
538 auto res = arith::DetectIterMap(
539 /*indices=*/realize->iter_values,
540 /*input_iters=*/loop_var_ranges,
541 /*predicate=*/realize->predicate,
542 /*check_level=*/arith::IterMapLevel::Surjective,
543 /*analyzer=*/analyzer,
544 /*simplify_trivial_iterators=*/false);
545 if (res->indices.empty()) {
546 return false;
547 }
548 for (const arith::IterSumExpr& sum_expr : res->indices) {
549 const Array<arith::IterSplitExpr>& args = sum_expr->args;
550 if (!args.empty() && !is_one(args[0]->scale)) {
551 return false;
552 }
553 }
554 return true;
555}
556
557void CheckPartialAffineBinding(const ScheduleState& self, Block block,
558 const Optional<StmtSRef>& high_exclusive) {
559 class NotAffineBindingError : public ScheduleError {
560 public:
561 explicit NotAffineBindingError(IRModule mod, Block block, Optional<StmtSRef> high_exclusive)
562 : mod_(std::move(mod)), block_(std::move(block)) {
563 if (high_exclusive.defined()) {
564 high_exclusive_loop_ = high_exclusive.value()->StmtAs<ForNode>();
565 }
566 }
567 String FastErrorString() const final {
568 std::ostringstream ss;
569 if (high_exclusive_loop_) {
570 ss << "ScheduleError: The block is required to have an partial affine binding under "
571 << high_exclusive_loop_->loop_var;
572 } else {
573 ss << "ScheduleError: The block is required to have an affine binding";
574 }
575 return ss.str();
576 }
577 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
578 std::ostringstream ss;
579 if (high_exclusive_loop_) {
580 ss << "The block {0} is required to have an partial affine binding under "
581 << high_exclusive_loop_->loop_var;
582 } else {
583 ss << "The block {0} is required to have an affine binding";
584 }
585 return ss.str();
586 }
587 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
588 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
589 IRModule mod_;
590 Block block_;
591 const ForNode* high_exclusive_loop_{nullptr};
592 };
593
594 StmtSRef block_sref = self->stmt2ref.at(block.get());
595 if (self->IsAffineBlockBinding(block_sref)) {
596 // check block cached state for global affineness
597 return;
598 }
599 if (block_sref->parent && high_exclusive.defined()) {
600 // if it is not of global affine binding, check affineness under high_exclusive,
601 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
602 Map<Var, Range> dom_map =
603 LoopDomainOfSRefTreePath(GetRef<StmtSRef>(block_sref->parent), high_exclusive);
604 if (IsAffineBinding(GetBlockRealize(self, block_sref), dom_map, &analyzer)) {
605 return;
606 }
607 }
608 throw NotAffineBindingError(self->mod, std::move(block), high_exclusive);
609}
610
611void CheckAffineBinding(const ScheduleState& self, Block block) {
612 CheckPartialAffineBinding(self, std::move(block), NullOpt);
613}

644Map<Var, Range> LoopDomainOfSRefTreePath(const StmtSRef& low_inclusive,
645 const Optional<StmtSRef>& high_exclusive,
646 const runtime::StorageScope& extra_relax_scope) {
647 Map<Var, Range> result;
648 const StmtSRefNode* p = low_inclusive.get();
649 const StmtSRefNode* limit = static_cast<const StmtSRefNode*>(high_exclusive.get());
650 for (; p != limit; p = p->parent) {
651 const ForNode* loop = p->StmtAs<ForNode>();
652 if (loop == nullptr) {
653 break;
654 }
655 result.Set(loop->loop_var, Range::FromMinExtent(loop->min, loop->extent));
656 }
657 if (extra_relax_scope.rank != runtime::StorageRank::kGlobal) {
658 for (; p; p = p->parent) {
659 if (const ForNode* loop = p->StmtAs<ForNode>()) {
660 if (loop->kind == ForKind::kThreadBinding) {
661 const String& thread_tag = loop->thread_binding.value()->thread_tag;
662 if (CanRelaxStorageUnderThread(extra_relax_scope,
663 runtime::ThreadScope::Create(thread_tag))) {
664 result.Set(loop->loop_var, Range::FromMinExtent(loop->min, loop->extent));
665 }
666 }
667 }
668 }
669 }
670 return result;
671}
672
673Map<Var, PrimExpr> GetBindings(const BlockRealize& realize) {
674 const BlockNode* block = realize->block.get();
675 const Array<IterVar>& all_lhs = block->iter_vars;
676 const Array<PrimExpr>& all_rhs = realize->iter_values;
677 ICHECK_EQ(all_lhs.size(), all_rhs.size());
678 Map<Var, PrimExpr> result;
679 for (int i = 0, n = all_lhs.size(); i < n; ++i) {
680 const IterVar& lhs = all_lhs[i];
681 const PrimExpr& rhs = all_rhs[i];
682 result.Set(lhs->var, rhs);
683 }
684 return result;
685}

687bool GetVarsTouchedByBlockIters(const BlockRealize& block_realize,
688 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* data_par_vars,
689 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* reduce_vars) {
690 Block block = block_realize->block;
691 ICHECK(block_realize->block.same_as(block))
692 << "ValueError: The input `block_realize` is required to be the exact BlockRealize of the "
693 "input block";
694
695 bool has_block_vars_of_other_types = false;
696 ICHECK_EQ(block->iter_vars.size(), block_realize->iter_values.size());
697 int n = static_cast<int>(block->iter_vars.size());
698 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
699 const IterVar& iter_var = block->iter_vars[i];
700 const PrimExpr& iter_value = block_realize->iter_values[i];
701 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>* set = nullptr;
702 if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
703 set = data_par_vars;
704 } else if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kCommReduce) {
705 set = reduce_vars;
706 } else {
707 has_block_vars_of_other_types = true;
708 }
709 if (set == nullptr) {
710 continue;
711 }
712 Array<Var> vars_in_binding = UndefinedVars(iter_value);
713 for (const Var& var : vars_in_binding) {
714 set->insert(var.get());
715 }
716 }
717
718 return has_block_vars_of_other_types;
719}

826BlockRealize GetBlockRealize(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
827 struct BlockRealizeFinder : public StmtVisitor {
828 explicit BlockRealizeFinder(const BlockNode* target_block)
829 : target_block(target_block), result(nullptr) {}
830
831 void VisitStmt(const Stmt& stmt) final {
832 if (result != nullptr) {
833 return;
834 }
835 StmtVisitor::VisitStmt(stmt);
836 }
837
838 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* block_realize) final {
839 if (block_realize->block.get() == target_block) {
840 result = block_realize;
841 }
842 // No need to visit recursively, since the deeper BlockRealizes must not be the result.
843 }
844
845 const BlockNode* target_block;
846 const BlockRealizeNode* result;
847 };
848
849 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
850 if (block_sref->parent == nullptr) {
851 const PrimFuncNode* func = GetRootPrimFunc(self->mod, block, nullptr);
852 return Downcast<BlockRealize>(func->body);
853 } else {
854 BlockRealizeFinder finder(block);
855 finder(GetRef<Stmt>(block_sref->parent->stmt));
856 ICHECK(finder.result != nullptr)
857 << "InternalError: Cannot find the BlockRealize of block " << GetRef<Block>(block);
858 return GetRef<BlockRealize>(finder.result);
859 }
860}
861
862IterVarType GetLoopIterType(const StmtSRef& loop_sref) {
863 const ForNode* loop = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loop_sref);
864 const Var& loop_var = loop->loop_var;
865 int n_spatial = 0;
866 int n_reduce = 0;
867 int n_other = 0;
868 auto f_visit = [&loop_var, &n_spatial, &n_reduce, &n_other](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
869 if (const auto* realize = obj.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
870 const BlockNode* block = realize->block.get();
871 // Number of block vars and their bindings
872 ICHECK_EQ(realize->iter_values.size(), block->iter_vars.size());
873 size_t n = realize->iter_values.size();
874 for (size_t i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
875 const IterVar& iter_var = block->iter_vars[i];
876 const PrimExpr& binding = realize->iter_values[i];
877 // Categorize the current block var
878 int* ref = nullptr;
879 if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
880 ref = &n_spatial;
881 } else if (iter_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kCommReduce) {
882 ref = &n_reduce;
883 } else {
884 ref = &n_other;
885 }
886 // Visit the binding to see if `loop_var` appears
887 PostOrderVisit(binding, [&ref, &loop_var](const ObjectRef& obj) -> void {
888 if (obj.same_as(loop_var)) {
889 (*ref) += 1;
890 }
891 });
892 }
893 return false;
894 }
895 return true;
896 };
897 PreOrderVisit(loop->body, f_visit);
898 if (n_other) {
899 return IterVarType::kOpaque;
900 } else if (n_spatial && n_reduce) {
901 return IterVarType::kOpaque;
902 } else if (n_reduce) {
903 return IterVarType::kCommReduce;
904 } else {
905 return IterVarType::kDataPar;
906 }
907}
908
909StmtSRef GetSRefLowestCommonAncestor(const Array<StmtSRef>& srefs) {
910 CHECK(!srefs.empty()) << "ValueError: The input array is required to have at least one sref";
911
912 std::unordered_map<const StmtSRefNode*, size_t> sref_visited_cnt;
913 for (const StmtSRef& sref : srefs) {
914 const StmtSRefNode* p = sref.get();
915 while (p != nullptr) {
916 ++sref_visited_cnt[p];
917 p = p->parent;
918 }
919 }
920 size_t n_sref = srefs.size();
921 const StmtSRefNode* p = srefs[0].get();
922 while (p != nullptr && sref_visited_cnt[p] != n_sref) {
923 p = p->parent;
924 }
925 ICHECK(p != nullptr);
926 return GetRef<StmtSRef>(p);
927}

933std::pair<Array<StmtSRef>, std::vector<int>> CollectComputeLocation(const ScheduleState& self,
934 const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
935 Array<StmtSRef> location_srefs;
936 std::vector<int> location_indices;
937
938 // Step 1. Add the "compute-root" candidate. Add the "compute-inline" candidate if the block can
939 // be inlined.
940 if (CanComputeInline(self, block_sref)) {
941 location_srefs.push_back(StmtSRef::InlineMark());
942 location_indices.push_back(-2);
943 }
944 location_srefs.push_back(StmtSRef::RootMark());
945 location_indices.push_back(-1);
946
947 // Step 2. If the block has no consumer, there is no more candidate.
948 Array<StmtSRef> consumers = GetConsumers(self, block_sref);
949 if (consumers.empty()) {
950 return std::make_pair(location_srefs, location_indices);
951 }
952
953 // Step 3. Get the deepest loop that the input block can be computed at (namely "boundary"). If
954 // such a loop cannot be found, there is no more candidate and we just return.
955 StmtSRef loop_boundary = consumers.size() > 1 ? GetSRefLowestCommonAncestor(consumers)
956 : GetRef<StmtSRef>(consumers[0]->parent);
957 if (loop_boundary->StmtAs<ForNode>() == nullptr) {
958 return std::make_pair(location_srefs, location_indices);
959 }
960
961 // Step 4. Collect the loops outside the first consumer and locate the boundary loop. The position
962 // of the boundary loop reveals the number of possible additional candidates.
963 Array<StmtSRef> loop_srefs = GetLoops(consumers[0]);
964 size_t lca_pos =
965 std::find(loop_srefs.begin(), loop_srefs.end(), loop_boundary) - loop_srefs.begin();
966 ICHECK_LT(lca_pos, loop_srefs.size());
967 size_t n_candidate = lca_pos + 1;
968
969 // Step 5. Find the position of the deepest data-parallel loop among the candidate loops. This
970 // position is used for removing the unwanted candidates from the perspective of performance.
971 std::vector<IterVarType> loop_iter_types;
972 loop_iter_types.reserve(n_candidate);
973 int i_last_datapar = -1;
974 for (size_t i = 0; i < n_candidate; ++i) {
975 // TODO(siyuan): improve the performance
976 IterVarType iter_type = GetLoopIterType(loop_srefs[i]);
977 loop_iter_types.push_back(iter_type);
978 if (iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
979 i_last_datapar = i;
980 }
981 }
982 // Step 6. Check and add the candidates in turn according to the following rules:
983 // - skip the unit loops (loops with extent 1);
984 // - do not consider the data-parallel loops after a not-data-parallel loop;
985 // - do not consider the trailing not-data-parallel loops.
986 location_srefs.reserve(n_candidate + 2);
987 location_indices.reserve(n_candidate + 2);
988 bool visited_reduce = false;
989 for (size_t i = 0; i < n_candidate; ++i) {
990 const int64_t* loop_extent = GetLoopIntExtent(loop_srefs[i]);
991 if (loop_extent != nullptr && *loop_extent == 1) {
992 continue;
993 }
994
995 if (loop_iter_types[i] == IterVarType::kDataPar) {
996 if (visited_reduce) {
997 break;
998 }
999 } else {
1000 visited_reduce = true;
1001 if (static_cast<int>(i) > i_last_datapar) {
1002 break;
1003 }
1004 }
1005 if (CanComputeAt(self, block_sref, loop_srefs[i], true)) {
1006 location_srefs.push_back(loop_srefs[i]);
1007 location_indices.push_back(i);
1008 }
1009 }
1010
1011 return std::make_pair(location_srefs, location_indices);
1012}

1035
1036ProducerConsumerSplit ProducerConsumerSplit::Find(
1037 const ScheduleState& self, const Array<Stmt>& subtrees,
1038 const Array<StmtSRef>& producer_block_srefs, const Array<StmtSRef>& consumer_block_srefs,
1039 std::unordered_map<const BlockNode*, const BlockRealizeNode*>* block2realize) {
1040 class InsertionPointNotFoundError : public ScheduleError {
1041 public:
1042 explicit InsertionPointNotFoundError(IRModule mod, int last_producer_position,
1043 int first_consumer_position)
1044 : mod_(mod),
1045 last_producer_position_(last_producer_position),
1046 first_consumer_position_(first_consumer_position) {}
1047
1048 String FastErrorString() const final {
1049 return "ScheduleError: Cannot find the insertion point that satisfies the producer-consumer "
1050 "constraint";
1051 }
1052
1053 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
1054 return "Cannot find the insertion point that satisfies the producer-consumer constraint. In "
1055 "0-based indexing, the last producer appears in subtree " +
1056 std::to_string(last_producer_position_) +
1057 ", and the first consumer appears in subtree " +
1058 std::to_string(first_consumer_position_);
1059 }
1060
1061 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
1062
1063 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {}; }
1064
1065 private:
1066 IRModule mod_;
1067 int last_producer_position_;
1068 int first_consumer_position_;
1069 };
1070
1071 class Finder : public StmtVisitor {
1072 public:
1073 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* realize) final {
1074 const BlockNode* block = realize->block.get();
1075 if (block2realize_) {
1076 block2realize_->emplace(block, realize);
1077 }
1078 if (producer_blocks_.count(block)) {
1079 ++this->n_producers_visited_;
1080 }
1081 if (consumer_blocks_.count(block)) {
1082 ++this->n_consumers_visited_;
1083 }
1084 }
1085
1086 std::unordered_map<const BlockNode*, const BlockRealizeNode*>* block2realize_;
1087 std::unordered_set<const StmtNode*> producer_blocks_;
1088 std::unordered_set<const StmtNode*> consumer_blocks_;
1089 int n_producers_visited_ = 0;
1090 int n_consumers_visited_ = 0;
1091 };
1092
1093 Finder finder;
1094 finder.block2realize_ = block2realize;
1095 // Set up the lookup table for producers
1096 finder.producer_blocks_.reserve(producer_block_srefs.size());
1097 for (const StmtSRef& block_sref : producer_block_srefs) {
1098 finder.producer_blocks_.insert(block_sref->stmt);
1099 }
1100 // Set up the lookup table for consumers
1101 finder.consumer_blocks_.reserve(consumer_block_srefs.size());
1102 for (const StmtSRef& block_sref : consumer_block_srefs) {
1103 finder.consumer_blocks_.insert(block_sref->stmt);
1104 }
1105 // Visit the subtrees
1106 int n = subtrees.size();
1107 int last_producer_position = -1;
1108 int first_consumer_position = n;
1109 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
1110 int n_producers_visited_before = finder.n_producers_visited_;
1111 int n_consumers_visited_before = finder.n_consumers_visited_;
1112 finder(subtrees[i]);
1113 // Check if the subtree contains at least a producer
1114 if (finder.n_producers_visited_ != n_producers_visited_before) {
1115 last_producer_position = i;
1116 }
1117 // Check if the subtree contains at least a consumer
1118 if (finder.n_consumers_visited_ != n_consumers_visited_before) {
1119 if (first_consumer_position == n) {
1120 first_consumer_position = i;
1121 }
1122 }
1123 }
1124 if (last_producer_position >= first_consumer_position) {
1125 throw InsertionPointNotFoundError(self->mod, last_producer_position, first_consumer_position);
1126 }
1127 return ProducerConsumerSplit{last_producer_position, //
1128 first_consumer_position, //
1129 finder.n_producers_visited_, //
1130 finder.n_consumers_visited_};
1131}

1135BufferRegion GetNthAccessBufferRegion(const ScheduleState& self, const Block& block, int n,
1136 BufferIndexType index_type) {
1137 class BufferIndexOutOfRangeError : public ScheduleError {
1138 public:
1139 explicit BufferIndexOutOfRangeError(IRModule mod, Block block, int buffer_index,
1140 BufferIndexType index_type)
1141 : mod_(std::move(mod)),
1142 block_(std::move(block)),
1143 buffer_index_(buffer_index),
1144 index_type_(index_type) {}
1145
1146 String FastErrorString() const final {
1147 if (index_type_ == BufferIndexType::kWrite) {
1148 return "ScheduleError: The input `buffer_index` is out of range. It is required to be in "
1149 "range "
1150 "[0, num_write_regions) where `num_write_regions` is the number of buffer regions "
1151 "written by the block.";
1152 } else {
1153 return "ScheduleError: The input `buffer_index` is out of range. It is required to be in "
1154 "range "
1155 "[0, num_read_regions) where `num_read_regions` is the number of buffer regions "
1156 "read by the block.";
1157 }
1158 }
1159
1160 String DetailRenderTemplate() const final {
1161 std::ostringstream os;
1162 size_t num =
1163 index_type_ == BufferIndexType::kWrite ? block_->writes.size() : block_->reads.size();
1164 os << "The block {0} has " << num << " " << BufferIndexType2Str(index_type_)
1165 << " regions, so `buffer_index` is required to be in [0, " << num
1166 << "). However, the input `buffer_index` is " << buffer_index_
1167 << ", which is out of the expected range.";
1168 return os.str();
1169 }
1170
1171 IRModule mod() const final { return mod_; }
1172 Array<ObjectRef> LocationsOfInterest() const final { return {block_}; }
1173
1174 private:
1175 IRModule mod_;
1176 Block block_;
1177 int buffer_index_;
1178 BufferIndexType index_type_;
1179 };
1180
1181 const Array<BufferRegion>& access_region =
1182 index_type == BufferIndexType::kWrite ? block->writes : block->reads;
1183
1184 if (n < 0 || static_cast<int>(access_region.size()) <= n) {
1185 throw BufferIndexOutOfRangeError(self->mod, block, n, index_type);
1186 }
1187 return access_region[n];
1188}

1194
1195std::pair<Optional<StmtSRef>, bool> GetBufferDefiningSite(const StmtSRef& block_sref,
1196 const Buffer& buffer) {
1197 // Climb up along the sref tree, and find the block where `buffer` is in alloc_buffers or
1198 // match_buffers.
1199 const StmtSRefNode* defining_site_sref = block_sref.get();
1200 while (defining_site_sref != nullptr) {
1201 const auto* block = defining_site_sref->StmtAs<BlockNode>();
1202 // If this sref is not a block sref, skip it.
1203 if (block == nullptr) {
1204 defining_site_sref = defining_site_sref->parent;
1205 continue;
1206 }
1207 // Try to find the buffer in `allloc_buffers`
1208 for (const Buffer& alloc_buffer : block->alloc_buffers) {
1209 if (buffer.same_as(alloc_buffer)) {
1210 return {GetRef<StmtSRef>(defining_site_sref), true};
1211 }
1212 }
1213 // We do not allow the buffer being defined in `match_buffer`.
1214 for (const MatchBufferRegion match_buffer : block->match_buffers) {
1215 if (buffer.same_as(match_buffer)) {
1216 return {GetRef<StmtSRef>(defining_site_sref), false};
1217 }
1218 }
1219 defining_site_sref = defining_site_sref->parent;
1220 }
1221 // If we cannot find the defining site block, it means that the buffer must be in the function's
1222 // buffer_map, which isn't an intermediate buffer.
1223 return {NullOpt, false};
1224}

1237bool HasOp(const Stmt& stmt, const Array<Op>& ops) {
1238 std::unordered_set<const Object*> op_set;
1239 op_set.reserve(ops.size());
1240 for (const Op& op : ops) {
1241 op_set.insert(op.operator->());
1242 }
1243 bool found = false;
1244 PreOrderVisit(stmt, [&found, &op_set](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
1245 if (found) {
1246 return false;
1247 }
1248 if (const auto* call = obj.as<CallNode>()) {
1249 if (op_set.count(call->op.operator->())) {
1250 found = true;
1251 }
1252 }
1253 return !found;
1254 });
1255 return found;
1256}
1257
1258bool HasIfThenElse(const Stmt& stmt) {
1259 bool has_branch = false;
1260 auto f_visit = [&has_branch](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
1261 if (has_branch) {
1262 // stop visiting
1263 return false;
1264 }
1265 if (const auto* realize = obj.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
1266 // Case 1: BlockRealize
1267 if (!is_one(realize->predicate)) {
1268 has_branch = true;
1269 }
1270 } else if (obj->IsInstance<IfThenElseNode>() || obj->IsInstance<SelectNode>()) {
1271 // Case 2: IfThenElse / Select
1272 has_branch = true;
1273 } else if (const auto* call = obj.as<CallNode>()) {
1274 // Case 3: Call the `if_then_else` operator
1275 static const Op& op_if_then_else = Op::Get("tir.if_then_else");
1276 if (call->op.same_as(op_if_then_else)) {
1277 has_branch = true;
1278 }
1279 }
1280 return !has_branch;
1281 };
1282 PreOrderVisit(stmt, f_visit);
1283 return has_branch;
1284}
1285
1286std::tuple</*exists=*/bool,
1287 /*surjective=*/bool,
1288 /*injective=*/bool,
1289 /*ordered=*/bool,
1290 /*no_const_read=*/bool,
1291 /*no_shift_read=*/bool>
1292AnalyzeReadWritePattern(const BufferRegion& read_region, const BufferRegion& write_region) {
1293 static constexpr const std::tuple<bool, bool, bool, bool, bool, bool> kNotExist =
1294 std::make_tuple(false, false, false, false, false, false);
1295 // Step 1. Extract the write indices
1296 int w_dim = write_region->buffer->shape.size();
1297 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, int> var2idx;
1298 var2idx.reserve(w_dim);
1299 for (int i = 0; i < w_dim; ++i) {
1300 const Range& dom = write_region->region[i];
1301 if (as_const_int(dom->extent) == nullptr) {
1302 return kNotExist;
1303 }
1304 if (const auto* v = dom->min.as<VarNode>()) {
1305 var2idx.emplace(v, i);
1306 } else {
1307 return kNotExist;
1308 }
1309 }
1310 // Step 2. Map each read index to a write index
1311 bool no_const_read = true;
1312 bool no_shift_read = true;
1313 int r_dim = read_region->buffer->shape.size();
1314 std::vector<int> mapped(r_dim, -1);
1315 for (int i = 0; i < r_dim; ++i) {
1316 const Range& dom = read_region->region[i];
1317 if (as_const_int(dom->extent) == nullptr) {
1318 return kNotExist;
1319 }
1320 // Case 1. Read index is a constant
1321 if (as_const_int(dom->min) != nullptr) {
1322 no_const_read = false;
1323 continue;
1324 }
1325 // Case 2. Read index cannot be recognized as `var +/- const`
1326 // where `var` is a write index and `const` is an optional constant shift
1327 Optional<IntImm> opt_const = NullOpt;
1328 const VarNode* var =
1329 static_cast<const VarNode*>(AnalyzeVarWithShift(dom->min, &opt_const).get());
1330 if (var == nullptr || !var2idx.count(var)) {
1331 return kNotExist;
1332 }
1333 // Case 3. Read index is `var +/- const`
1334 mapped[i] = var2idx.at(var);
1335 if (opt_const.defined()) {
1336 no_shift_read = false;
1337 }
1338 }
1339 // Step 3. Check if the mapping is ordered, and count how many times each var is mapped
1340 std::vector<int> mapped_counter(w_dim, 0);
1341 bool ordered = true;
1342 int last_mapped = -1;
1343 for (int i : mapped) {
1344 if (i != -1) {
1345 ++mapped_counter[i];
1346 if (last_mapped != -1 && last_mapped > i) {
1347 ordered = false;
1348 }
1349 last_mapped = i;
1350 }
1351 }
1352 // Step 4. Check if the mapping is surjective or injective
1353 // Surjective: each write index is mapped at least once
1354 // Injective: each write index is mapped at most once
1355 bool surjective = true;
1356 bool injective = true;
1357 for (int cnt : mapped_counter) {
1358 if (cnt == 0) {
1359 surjective = false;
1360 } else if (cnt >= 2) {
1361 injective = false;
1362 }
1363 }
1364 return std::make_tuple(/*exist=*/true, surjective, injective, ordered, no_const_read,
1365 no_shift_read);
1366}

1390 };

1399bool IsSpatial(const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
1400 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1401 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
1402 if (iter_var->iter_type != IterVarType::kDataPar) {
1403 return false;
1404 }
1405 }
1406 return true;

1409bool IsTrivialBinding(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
1410 TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1411 Array<StmtSRef> loops = GetLoops(block_sref);
1412 Array<PrimExpr> binds = GetBlockRealize(self, block_sref)->iter_values;
1413 if (loops.size() != binds.size()) {
1414 return false;
1415 }
1416 for (int i = 0, n = loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1417 const ForNode* loop = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loops[i]);
1418 if (binds[i].get() != loop->loop_var.get()) {
1419 return false;
1420 }
1421 }
1422 return true;
1423}
1424
1425bool NeedsMultiLevelTiling(const ScheduleState& self, const StmtSRef& block_sref) {
1426 if (HasBeenMultiLevelTiled(block_sref)) {
1427 return false;
1428 }
1429 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1430 if (block->writes.size() != 1 || block->reads.empty() || IsSpatial(block_sref) ||
1431 !IsTrivialBinding(self, block_sref)) {
1432 return false;
1433 }
1434 const BufferNode* write_buffer = block->writes[0]->buffer.get();
1435 // Step 1. Sort out spatial block variables. Skip the block iters of domain [0, 1), since such
1436 // block iters distracts the following check of the unused block iters.
1437 std::vector<const VarNode*> spatial_block_vars;
1438 spatial_block_vars.reserve(block->iter_vars.size());
1439 for (const IterVar& block_var : block->iter_vars) {
1440 const int64_t* dom_min = as_const_int(block_var->dom->min);
1441 const int64_t* dom_extent = as_const_int(block_var->dom->extent);
1442 bool has_trivial_dom =
1443 dom_min != nullptr && dom_extent != nullptr && *dom_min == 0 && *dom_extent == 1;
1444 if (block_var->iter_type == IterVarType::kDataPar && !has_trivial_dom) {
1445 spatial_block_vars.push_back(block_var->var.get());
1446 }
1447 }
1448 // Step 2. Enumerate each read region, check the number of block vars that are not used
1449 // to index the read region
1450 int total_unused_block_vars = 0;
1451 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> read_buffers;
1452 read_buffers.reserve(block->reads.size());
1453 for (const BufferRegion& buffer_region : block->reads) {
1454 const BufferNode* buffer = buffer_region->buffer.get();
1455 const Array<Range>& regions = buffer_region->region;
1456 // Step 2.1. Duplication of read buffers are not allowed
1457 if (read_buffers.insert(buffer).second == false) {
1458 return false;
1459 }
1460 // Step 2.2. Skip the reduction buffer
1461 if (buffer == write_buffer) {
1462 continue;
1463 }
1464 // Step 2.3. Collect the block vars that are used to index the read region
1465 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*> vars;
1466 for (const Range& range : regions) {
1467 if (as_const_int(range->extent) == nullptr) {
1468 return false;
1469 }
1470 for (const Var& var : UndefinedVars(range->min)) {
1471 vars.insert(var.get());
1472 }
1473 }
1474 // Step 2.4. Check if the block vars are not used to index the read region
1475 int n_unused_block_vars = 0;
1476 for (const VarNode* block_var : spatial_block_vars) {
1477 if (vars.count(block_var) == 0) {
1478 ++n_unused_block_vars;
1479 }
1480 }
1481 total_unused_block_vars += n_unused_block_vars;
1482 }
1483 return total_unused_block_vars >= 1;
1484}

1486bool IsSpatialPrimFunc(const PrimFunc& func) {
1487 bool result = true;
1488 PreOrderVisit(func->body, [&result](const ObjectRef& obj) {
1489 if (result == false) {
1490 return false;
1491 }
1492 if (const auto* block = obj.as<BlockNode>()) {
1493 for (const IterVar& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
1494 if (iter_var->iter_type != IterVarType::kDataPar) {
1495 result = false;
1496 return false;
1497 }
1498 }
1499 }
1500 return true;
1501 });
1502 return result;
1503}
1504
1505std::pair<int64_t, int64_t> GetCumulativeSpaceAndReductionLength(const tir::ScheduleState& self,
1506 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref) {
1507 Array<tir::StmtSRef> loops = tir::GetLoops(block_sref);
1508 int64_t cum_space_len = 1, cum_reduce_len = 1;
1509 /*
1510 * Return (-1, -1) if
1511 * 1. there is some loop with type other than kDataPar and kCommReduce;
1512 * 2. there is some loop which is dynamic.
1513 */
1514 for (const tir::StmtSRef& loop_sref : loops) {
1515 tir::IterVarType type = GetLoopIterType(loop_sref);
1516 if (type == tir::kDataPar) {
1517 const int64_t* extent = GetLoopIntExtent(loop_sref);
1518 if (*extent != -1) {
1519 cum_space_len *= *extent;
1520 } else {
1521 return std::make_pair(-1, -1);
1522 }
1523 } else if (type == tir::kCommReduce) {
1524 const int64_t* extent = GetLoopIntExtent(loop_sref);
1525 if (*extent != -1) {
1526 cum_reduce_len *= *extent;
1527 } else {
1528 return std::make_pair(-1, -1);
1529 }
1530 } else {
1531 return std::make_pair(-1, -1);
1532 }
1533 }
1534 return std::make_pair(cum_space_len, cum_reduce_len);
1535}
1536
1537bool NeedsRFactorOrCrossThreadReduction(const tir::ScheduleState& self, //
1538 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref, //
1539 int64_t max_parallel_extent, //
1540 int64_t max_parallel_basic) {
1541 const BlockNode* block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1542 Array<tir::StmtSRef> loops = tir::GetLoops(block_sref);
1543
1544 // Cond 1. The block must have at lease one write buffer
1545 if (block->writes.size() == 0) {
1546 return false;
1547 }
1548
1549 // Cond 2. The block is a reduction block and has trivial binding.
1550 const StmtSRef& scope_sref = GetScopeRoot(self, block_sref,
1551 /*require_stage_pipeline=*/false);
1552 if (!IsReductionBlock(self, block_sref, scope_sref) //
1553 || !IsTrivialBinding(self, block_sref) //
1554 || HasBeenMultiLevelTiled(block_sref)) {
1555 return false;
1556 }
1557
1558 // Cond 3. Every the loop axis must be either spatial axis or reduction axis.
1559 for (const tir::StmtSRef& loop_sref : loops) {
1560 const tir::IterVarType& type = GetLoopIterType(loop_sref);
1561 if (type != tir::kDataPar && type != tir::kCommReduce) {
1562 return false;
1563 }
1564 }
1565
1566 // Cond 4. Whether there is at least one reduction loop.
1567 // Cond 5. The loops are continuous, and the body of the innermost loop is exactly the block.
1568 bool has_reduction_loop = false;
1569 for (size_t i = 0; i < loops.size(); ++i) {
1570 // Cond 4.
1571 if (GetLoopIterType(loops[i]) == tir::kCommReduce) {
1572 has_reduction_loop = true;
1573 }
1574
1575 // Cond 5.
1576 const ForNode* loop_i = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loops[i]);
1577 if (i < loops.size() - 1) {
1578 const ForNode* loop_i1 = TVM_SREF_TO_FOR(loops[i + 1]);
1579 if (loop_i->body.get() != loop_i1) {
1580 return false;
1581 }
1582 } else {
1583 const auto* block_realize = loop_i->body.as<tir::BlockRealizeNode>();
1584 if (!block_realize || block_realize->block.get() != block) {
1585 return false;
1586 }
1587 }
1588 }
1589 if (!has_reduction_loop) {
1590 return false;
1591 }
1592
1593 // Cond 6. Can successfully calculating the cumulative loop length.
1594 auto [cum_space_len, cum_reduce_len] = GetCumulativeSpaceAndReductionLength(self, block_sref);
1595 if (cum_space_len == -1 || cum_reduce_len == -1) {
1596 return false;
1597 }
1598
1599 // Cond 7.
1600 if (NeedsMultiLevelTiling(self, block_sref)) {
1601 // Do not use rfactor/cross-thread-reduction if we have enough parallelism on spatial loops.
1602 return !(cum_space_len >= cum_reduce_len || cum_space_len > max_parallel_extent);
1603 } else {
1604 // Always try rfactor/cross-thread-reduction for other reduction blocks.
1605 return cum_reduce_len > 1;
1606 }
1607}

1610 auto simplified = analyzer->Simplify(expr);
1611 if (simplified->IsInstance<IntImmNode>()) {
1612 return expr;
1613 } else {
1614 return simplified;
1615 }

1618TVM_REGISTER_NODE_TYPE(TensorizeInfoNode);
1619
1620/*! \brief Auxiliary data structure of information extracted from tensor intrin description */
1621struct TensorIntrinDescInfo {
1622 /*! \brief The block of the description function, which is the (unique) direct child of the root
1623 * block.
1624 */
1625 const BlockRealizeNode* desc_block = nullptr;
1626 /*! \brief The loops of the description function, in the order from outer loops to inner ones. */
1627 std::vector<const tir::ForNode*> desc_loops;
1628 /*! \brief The loop variables. */
1629 std::unordered_set<const tir::VarNode*> desc_loop_vars;
1630};
1631
1632/*!
1633 * \brief Extract auxilary information from the tensor intrin description.
1634 * \param analyze The arithmetic analyzer
1635 * \param desc_func The description PrimFunc
1636 * \return The auxilary information
1637 */
1638TensorIntrinDescInfo ExtractTensorIntrinDescInfo(arith::Analyzer* analyzer,
1639 const PrimFunc& desc_func) {
1640 TensorIntrinDescInfo info;
1641 const auto* desc_scope_realize = desc_func->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>();
1642 ICHECK(desc_scope_realize);
1643 {
1644 auto f_visit = [&](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
1645 // Extract the block
1646 if (const auto* block = obj.as<BlockRealizeNode>()) {
1647 info.desc_block = block;
1648 return false;
1649 }
1650 // Extract the loops
1651 if (const auto* loop = obj.as<ForNode>()) {
1652 info.desc_loops.push_back(loop);
1653 info.desc_loop_vars.insert(loop->loop_var.get());
1654 if (!analyzer->CanProve(loop->min == 0)) {
1655 return false;
1656 }
1657 }
1658 return true;
1659 };
1660 tir::PostOrderVisit(desc_scope_realize->block->body, f_visit);
1661 std::reverse(info.desc_loops.begin(), info.desc_loops.end());
1662 ICHECK(info.desc_block);
1663 }
1664 return info;
1665}
1666
1667Optional<TensorizeInfo> GetTensorizeLoopMapping(const tir::ScheduleState& self,
1668 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref,
1669 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func,
1670 bool allow_padding) {
1671 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
1672 const tir::BlockRealize& block = tir::GetBlockRealize(self, block_sref);
1673 // Step 1. Analyze desc_func, extract its block, loops and loop vars
1674 TensorIntrinDescInfo desc_info = ExtractTensorIntrinDescInfo(&analyzer, desc_func);
1675 // Step 2. Collect loops from block_sref
1676 const tir::StmtSRef& scope_sref = GetScopeRoot(self, block_sref, false);
1677 TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_sref);
1678 std::vector<const tir::ForNode*> block_loops;
1679 std::unordered_set<const tir::VarNode*> block_loop_vars;
1680 {
1681 for (const tir::StmtSRefNode* loop_sref = block_sref->parent;; loop_sref = loop_sref->parent) {
1682 const auto* loop = loop_sref->StmtAs<tir::ForNode>();
1683 if (loop == nullptr || loop->body->IsInstance<tir::SeqStmtNode>()) {
1684 break;
1685 }
1686 block_loops.push_back(loop);
1687 block_loop_vars.insert(loop->loop_var.get());
1688 if (!analyzer.CanProve(loop->min == 0)) {
1689 return NullOpt;
1690 }
1691 }
1692 std::reverse(block_loops.begin(), block_loops.end());
1693 }
1694 // Step 3. Map from block loops to desc block loops
1695 const std::vector<const ForNode*>& desc_loops = desc_info.desc_loops;
1696 const std::unordered_set<const VarNode*>& desc_loop_vars = desc_info.desc_loop_vars;
1697 const BlockRealizeNode* desc_block = desc_info.desc_block;
1698 ObjectPtr<TensorizeInfoNode> ret = make_object<TensorizeInfoNode>();
1699 const int n_block_vars = block->iter_values.size();
1700 const int n_desc_vars = desc_block->iter_values.size();
1701 const int offset = n_block_vars - n_desc_vars;
1702
1703 std::unordered_map<int, int> block_index_to_padding; // padding of each block iter if necessary
1704
1705 if (offset < 0) {
1706 return NullOpt;
1707 }
1708
1709 const std::vector<IterVarType> iter_types_block = GetBlockVarTypes(block_sref);
1710 const std::vector<IterVarType> iter_types_desc = GetBlockVarTypes(desc_block->block.get());
1711
1712 ICHECK(desc_loops.size() == static_cast<size_t>(n_desc_vars));
1713 ICHECK(block_loops.size() == iter_types_block.size());
1714
1715 // We assume that the orders of iter_vars in the target and the desc block are consistent.
1716 // Based on that assumption, the following logic supports arbitrary permutations of a loop order,
1717 // such as
1718
1719 // for k:
1720 // for i:
1721 // for j:
1722 // C[i, j] += A[i, k] * B[k, j]
1723
1724 // or
1725
1726 // for i:
1727 // for j:
1728 // for k:
1729 // C[i, j] += A[i, k] * B[k, j]
1730
1731 int next_block_ind = block_loops.size() - 1;
1732 for (int i_desc = n_desc_vars - 1; i_desc >= 0; --i_desc) {
1733 // Step 3.1. Find the corresponding loop of the i_desc-th block var of desc
1734 const PrimExpr& desc_bind = desc_block->iter_values[i_desc];
1735 const tir::ForNode* desc_loop = nullptr;
1736 IterVarType iter_type_desc = iter_types_desc[i_desc];
1737 for (int i = 0, n = desc_loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1738 // Check if desc_bind = loops[i]->loop_var + stuff-irrelevant-of-loop-vars
1739 PrimExpr residual = analyzer.Simplify(desc_bind - desc_loops[i]->loop_var);
1740 if (!UsesVar(residual,
1741 [&desc_loop_vars](const VarNode* var) { return desc_loop_vars.count(var); })) {
1742 desc_loop = desc_loops[i];
1743 iter_type_desc = iter_types_desc[i];
1744 break;
1745 }
1746 }
1747 if (desc_loop == nullptr || desc_loop->extent.as<IntImmNode>() == nullptr) {
1748 return NullOpt;
1749 }
1750
1751 const IntImmNode* int_desc_extent = desc_loop->extent.as<IntImmNode>();
1752
1753 // Step 3.2. Find the corresponding iter_value of the target block with a matching iterator type
1754 PrimExpr block_bind;
1755 int current_block_ind = next_block_ind;
1756 for (; current_block_ind >= 0; --current_block_ind) {
1757 if (iter_types_block[current_block_ind] == iter_type_desc) {
1758 next_block_ind = current_block_ind - 1;
1759 block_bind = block->iter_values[current_block_ind];
1760 break;
1761 }
1762 }
1763
1764 if (!block_bind.defined()) return NullOpt;
1765
1766 // Step 3.3. Find the corresponding loop of the target block
1767 for (int i = 0, n = block_loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1768 // Check if block_bind = block_loops[i]->loop_var + stuff-irrelevant-of-loop-vars
1769 const tir::ForNode* block_loop = block_loops[i];
1770 const tir::StmtSRef& block_loop_sref = self->stmt2ref[block_loop];
1771 // Skip i-th loop if it has already been mapped
1772 if (ret->loop_map.find(block_loop_sref) != ret->loop_map.end()) continue;
1773
1774 PrimExpr residual = analyzer.Simplify(block_bind - block_loops[i]->loop_var);
1775 if (UsesVar(residual,
1776 [&block_loop_vars](const VarNode* var) { return block_loop_vars.count(var); })) {
1777 continue;
1778 }
1779 // padding is allowed only when the block has trivial bindings
1780 if (allow_padding && !is_zero(residual)) {
1781 allow_padding = false;
1782 }
1783
1784 const IntImmNode* int_block_extent = block_loops[i]->extent.as<IntImmNode>();
1785
1786 // Check divisibility
1787 if (!int_block_extent) {
1788 return NullOpt;
1789 }
1790 int64_t remainder = int_block_extent->value % int_desc_extent->value;
1791 if (remainder != 0) {
1792 if (allow_padding) {
1793 // If the block loop is not divisible by the desc loop, we pad the block loop to make it
1794 // divisible if padding is allowed.
1795 block_index_to_padding[current_block_ind] = int_desc_extent->value - remainder;
1796 } else {
1797 return NullOpt;
1798 }
1799 }
1800
1801 ret->loop_map.Set(block_loop_sref, GetRef<tir::For>(desc_loop));
1802 break;
1803 }
1804 }
1805
1806 for (int i = 0, n = desc_loops.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1807 ret->desc_loop_indexer.Set(GetRef<tir::For>(desc_loops[i]), Integer(i));
1808 }
1809 if (!block_index_to_padding.empty()) {
1810 if (!allow_padding) {
1811 return NullOpt;
1812 }
1813 Array<Integer> paddings;
1814 for (int i = 0, n = block->block->iter_vars.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1815 const IterVar& iter_var = block->block->iter_vars[i];
1816 if (auto it = block_index_to_padding.find(i); it != block_index_to_padding.end()) {
1817 paddings.push_back(IntImm(iter_var->var.dtype(), it->second));
1818 } else {
1819 paddings.push_back(IntImm(iter_var->var.dtype(), 0));
1820 }
1821 }
1822 ret->block_iter_paddings = std::move(paddings);
1823 }
1824
1825 return TensorizeInfo(ret);
1826}

1829TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("tir.schedule.GetTensorizeLoopMapping")
1830 .set_body_typed([](Schedule sch, BlockRV block, PrimFunc desc_func, bool allow_padding) {
1831 return GetTensorizeLoopMapping(sch->state(), sch->GetSRef(block), desc_func, allow_padding);

1834/******** Auto Tensorization ********/
1835
1836/*! \brief IndexMap proposer for layout transformation in auto tensorization. */
1837class AutoTensorizeMappingProposer {
1838 public:
1839 static Array<IndexMap> ProposeMappings(const AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor,
1840 arith::Analyzer* analyzer) {
1841 AutoTensorizeMappingProposer proposer(extractor, analyzer);
1842 proposer.CollectFeasibleSet();
1843 return proposer.ProposeAllFuseMapping();
1844 }
1845
1846 private:
1847 explicit AutoTensorizeMappingProposer(const AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor,
1848 arith::Analyzer* analyzer)
1849 : extractor_(extractor), analyzer_(analyzer) {}
1850
1851 using VarSet = std::unordered_set<Var, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual>;
1852
1853 void CollectFeasibleSet() {
1854 // Collect the set of potential iter var mapping between the workload and the tensor intrin.
1855 // We analyze the appearance of each variable in the buffer indices of each buffer on LHS and
1856 // RHS. The appearance of a variable in the buffer indices is encoded as bit-masks (BufferMask).
1857 // Variables on the LHS and the RHS with the same bit-mask and the same iter type are potential
1858 // mappings.
1859 //
1860 // For example, consider the conv2d case. We will try to match the workload
1861 // conv2d[n, h, w, c] = sum_{rh, rw, rc} X[n, h + rh, w + rw, c + rc] * W[rh, rw, rc, c]
1862 // against a matmul tensor intrin
1863 // C[m, n] = sum_{k} A[m, k] * B[k, n]
1864 // First we extract the correspondence of the buffers: conv2d <=> C, A <=> X, B <=> W.
1865 // Then for each variable, we extract the buffers where it is used for indexing.
1866 // Take the variable m on the RHS as an example. m is used to index buffer A and C. On the LHS,
1867 // we will find the variables used to index only the exact corresponding buffers conv2d and X
1868 // (the variable is not allowed to index other buffers). In this case, n, h, w is used to index
1869 // both buffer conv2d and W, and not in other buffers. Therefore, {n, h, w} <=> m is a potential
1870 // mapping.
1871
1872 // Note: the mapping is not unique when multiple variables on RHS has the same bit-mask.
1873 // This is currently not supported.
1874
1875 using BufferMask = std::vector<bool>;
1876
1877 // Step 1: Assign an index to each buffer in LHS and RHS
1878 std::unordered_map<Buffer, int, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectEqual> rhs_buffer_index;
1879 std::unordered_map<Buffer, int, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectEqual> lhs_buffer_index;
1880 {
1881 int i = 0;
1882 for (const auto& kv : extractor_->rhs_buffer_map_) {
1883 const Buffer& rhs_buffer = kv.first;
1884 const Buffer& lhs_buffer = kv.second;
1885 rhs_buffer_index[rhs_buffer] = i;
1886 lhs_buffer_index[lhs_buffer] = i;
1887 ++i;
1888 }
1889 }
1890
1891 // Step 2: Compute the buffer mask
1892 ICHECK_EQ(rhs_buffer_index.size(), lhs_buffer_index.size());
1893 int num_buffers = rhs_buffer_index.size();
1894 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, std::vector<bool>> rhs_buffer_masks, lhs_buffer_masks;
1895 // helper function to initialize or update the buffer mask
1896 auto update_mask = [&](const VarNode* var,
1897 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, std::vector<bool>>* masks, int i) {
1898 if (!masks->count(var)) {
1899 (*masks)[var].resize(num_buffers);
1900 }
1901 (*masks)[var][i] = true;
1902 };
1903
1904 for (const auto& it : extractor_->rhs_buffer_indices_map_) {
1905 const Buffer& rhs_buffer = it.first;
1906 for (const PrimExpr& rhs_index : it.second) {
1907 if (const VarNode* var_node = rhs_index.as<VarNode>()) {
1908 update_mask(var_node, &rhs_buffer_masks, rhs_buffer_index.at(rhs_buffer));
1909 } else {
1910 LOG(FATAL) << "ValueError: Buffer index " << rhs_index
1911 << " other that variables in tensor intrinsics is not supported.";
1912 }
1913 }
1914
1915 auto lhs_buffer_it = extractor_->rhs_buffer_map_.find(rhs_buffer);
1916 ICHECK(lhs_buffer_it != extractor_->rhs_buffer_map_.end());
1917 const Buffer& lhs_buffer = lhs_buffer_it->second;
1918 for (const PrimExpr& index : extractor_->lhs_buffer_indices_map_.at(lhs_buffer)) {
1919 PreOrderVisit(index, [&](const ObjectRef& obj) -> bool {
1920 if (const VarNode* var = obj.as<VarNode>()) {
1921 update_mask(var, &lhs_buffer_masks, lhs_buffer_index.at(lhs_buffer));
1922 }
1923 return true;
1924 });
1925 }
1926 }
1927
1928 // Step 3: Find variables on LHS and RHS with the same buffer mask. Ensure LHS and RHS vars
1929 // have the same iter type.
1930 std::unordered_map<BufferMask, VarSet> mask_to_rhs_vars;
1931 for (const auto& kv : rhs_buffer_masks) {
1932 const VarNode* rhs_var = kv.first;
1933 const BufferMask& mask = kv.second;
1934 mask_to_rhs_vars[mask].insert(GetRef<Var>(rhs_var));
1935 }
1936 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, IterVarType> rhs_var_iter_type;
1937 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->rhs_iters_) {
1938 rhs_var_iter_type.emplace(iter->var.get(), iter->iter_type);
1939 }
1940 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->lhs_iters_) {
1941 auto& potential_mappings = lhs_feasible_vars_[iter->var];
1942 VarSet rhs_candidates = mask_to_rhs_vars[lhs_buffer_masks[iter->var.get()]];
1943 std::copy_if(
1944 rhs_candidates.begin(), rhs_candidates.end(),
1945 std::inserter(potential_mappings, potential_mappings.begin()),
1946 [&](const Var& var) { return rhs_var_iter_type.at(var.get()) == iter->iter_type; });
1947 }
1948 }
1949
1950 Array<IndexMap> ProposeAllFuseMapping() {
1951 // Now we have calcuated potential mapping for each iter var on LHS. For iters on LHS mapped to
1952 // the same iter on RHS, they will be fused in the original order in LHS block iters. We will
1953 // generate IndexMap to represent such fusion on LHS. For example, if n, h, w on LHS are mapped
1954 // to the same iter var on RHS, we will produce index map `lambda n, h, w: fuse(n, h, w)`, where
1955 // fuse(v0, .., vn) = ((v0 * v1_extent + v1) + ... ) * vn_extent + vn
1956
1957 // the parameters of the result index map, each parameter corresponds to a LHS iter
1958 Array<Var> index_map_src;
1959 // the outputs of the result index map
1960 Array<PrimExpr> index_map_tgt;
1961
1962 // Step 1: Collect extents of LHS iters and prepare the initial indices of the IndexMap
1963 Map<Var, PrimExpr> lhs_iter_extents;
1964 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->lhs_iters_) {
1965 lhs_iter_extents.Set(iter->var, iter->dom->extent);
1966 index_map_src.push_back(iter->var.copy_with_suffix(""));
1967 }
1968
1969 // Step 2: Each iter on RHS has a group of corresponding iters on LHS. Initialize the fusion
1970 // result for each group of iters on LHS.
1971 Map<Var, PrimExpr> fused_lhs_iters;
1972 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->rhs_iters_) {
1973 fused_lhs_iters.Set(iter->var, 0);
1974 }
1975
1976 // Step 3: Fuse LHS iters mapped to the same RHS iter
1977 std::unordered_set<Var, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> used_rhs_vars;
1978 for (size_t i = 0; i < extractor_->lhs_iters_.size(); ++i) {
1979 const Var& lhs_iter_var = extractor_->lhs_iters_[i]->var;
1980 const VarSet& rhs_candidates = lhs_feasible_vars_[lhs_iter_var];
1981 if (rhs_candidates.empty()) {
1982 // put unmapped iters at the beginning
1983 index_map_tgt.push_back(index_map_src[i]);
1984 } else if (rhs_candidates.size() == 1) {
1985 Var rhs_var = *rhs_candidates.begin();
1986 PrimExpr fused_lhs = fused_lhs_iters.at(rhs_var);
1987 PrimExpr updated_fused_lhs =
1988 fused_lhs * lhs_iter_extents.at(lhs_iter_var) + index_map_src[i];
1989 fused_lhs_iters.Set(rhs_var, updated_fused_lhs);
1990 used_rhs_vars.insert(rhs_var);
1991 } else {
1992 // non-unique mapping is not supported
1993 return {};
1994 }
1995 }
1996 for (const auto& iter : extractor_->rhs_iters_) {
1997 if (!used_rhs_vars.count(iter->var)) {
1998 return {};
1999 }
2000 index_map_tgt.push_back(analyzer_->Simplify(fused_lhs_iters[iter->var]));
2001 }
2002 // At most one mapping is supported.
2003 return {IndexMap(index_map_src, index_map_tgt)};
2004 }
2005
2006 private:
2007 // The extractor that has extracted information for auto tensorization from the workload and the
2008 // tensor intrin.
2009 const AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor_;
2010 // The arithmetic analyzer.
2011 arith::Analyzer* analyzer_;
2012 /*! \brief Potential mappings on RHS for each variable on LHS */
2013 std::unordered_map<Var, VarSet, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> lhs_feasible_vars_;
2014};
2015
2016bool CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(const ScheduleState& state, const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref,
2017 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func,
2018 AutoTensorizeComparator* extractor) {
2019 // Step 1. Analyze desc_func, extract its block, loops and loop vars
2020 // Step 2. Check if `desc_block` matches `block`
2021 // Ignore the scope of buffers when comparing, since we can do cache_read/write
2022 const BlockRealize& block = tir::GetBlockRealize(state, block_sref);
2023 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
2024 auto desc_info = tir::ExtractTensorIntrinDescInfo(&analyzer, desc_func);
2025
2026 return extractor->VisitStmt(block->block, desc_info.desc_block->block);
2027}
2028
2029bool CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(const tir::Schedule& sch, const tir::BlockRV& block_rv,
2030 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func) {
2031 AutoTensorizeComparator extractor(sch->state()->mod);
2032 return CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(sch->state(), sch->GetSRef(block_rv), desc_func, &extractor);
2033}
2034
2035Optional<AutoTensorizeMappingInfo> GetAutoTensorizeMappingInfo(const tir::ScheduleState& self,
2036 const tir::StmtSRef& block_sref,
2037 const tir::PrimFunc& desc_func) {
2038 AutoTensorizeComparator extractor(self->mod);
2039 if (!CheckAutoTensorizeApplicable(self, block_sref, desc_func, &extractor)) {
2040 return NullOpt;
2041 }
2042 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
2043 Array<IndexMap> mappings = AutoTensorizeMappingProposer::ProposeMappings(&extractor, &analyzer);
2044 if (mappings.empty()) {
2045 return NullOpt;
2046 }
2047 ObjectPtr<AutoTensorizeMappingInfoNode> ret = make_object<AutoTensorizeMappingInfoNode>();
2048 ret->mappings = std::move(mappings);
2049 ret->lhs_buffer_map = std::move(extractor.lhs_buffer_map_);
2050 ret->rhs_buffer_indices = std::move(extractor.rhs_buffer_indices_map_);
2051 ret->lhs_iters = std::move(extractor.lhs_iters_);
2052 ret->rhs_iters = std::move(extractor.rhs_iters_);
2053 return AutoTensorizeMappingInfo(ret);
2054}
